<script>
/* =============================================================================
   SECTION 9 \u2014 Heritage Configurator engine
   8 user choices (Housing \u00B7 Voltage \u00B7 Finish \u00B7 Optic \u00B7 Mount \u00B7 Photocell \u00B7
   Sensor \u2014 plus auto-locked -3H1 CCTSELECT capability) \u00B7 2 field-set DIP
   (WATTSELECT, CCTSELECT) \u2014 informational only.
   SKU pattern (per James 2026-05-02 PM):
       LSBX3W{housing}-3H1-{voltage}{finish}{optic}/RB3{/mount?}{/PS?}{/MSP-?}
   Examples:
       LSBX3W150-3H1-UD3/RB3                      \u2190 default \u00B7 150W DIP \u00B7 5000K DIP
       LSBX3W150-3H1-UD3/RB3/UA                   \u2190 + universal mount adder
       LSBX3W150-3H1-UD3/RB3/UA/PS                \u2190 + photocell
       LSBX3W150-3H1-UD3/RB3/UA/PS/MSP-ACS        \u2190 fully-loaded
       LSBX3W300-3H1-HD3/RB3/SP/MSP-NLC           \u2190 HV + slip-pole + SILVAIR
       LSBX3W150-3H1-URAL70163/RB3                \u2190 custom RAL 7016 \u00B7 Type III
   Datasheet rated: 150 lm/W flat (5000K).
   LM-79 measured: dispersion across cells \u2014 peak 175 lm/W (70W @ 4000K),
                   floor 127 lm/W (300W @ 3000K \u00B7 5000K). See Section 7.
   CONSTRAINT: H voltage is only valid on LSBX3W300. When housing flips to
   LSBX3W150, voltage auto-snaps to U.
